---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 1 — the HERO "THE LSM PATH" banner: the
 * write path (memtable → flush → immutable SSTables → compact → merged SSTable)
 * and the "scored on 3 amps" scoreboard.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arw (fill #6b675f) and #arwA (fill #7a1f12) markers this figure references
 * via marker-end="url(#…)" are inlined here in a local <defs> so it resolves
 * standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The LSM write path: writes hit the memtable, flush to immutable SSTables on disk, and compaction merges SSTables in the background dropping shadowed and deleted keys"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="56"
                width="120"
                height="52"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="74" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >memtable</text
            >
            <text x="74" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >in-RAM, sorted</text
            >
            <text x="74" y="42" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111110">writes ↓</text>
            <line x1="134" y1="82" x2="172" y2="82" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="153" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">flush</text>
            <!-- SSTables on disk -->
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a">
                <rect x="176" y="50" width="96" height="20" rx="4"></rect><rect
                    x="176"
                    y="74"
                    width="96"
                    height="20"
                    rx="4"></rect><rect x="176" y="98" width="96" height="20" rx="4"></rect>
            </g>
            <g font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a" text-anchor="middle"
                ><text x="224" y="64">SSTable</text><text x="224" y="88">SSTable</text><text
                    x="224"
                    y="112">SSTable</text
                ></g
            >
            <text x="224" y="136" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >immutable, on disk</text
            >
            <line x1="278" y1="84" x2="320" y2="84" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text x="299" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12">compact</text>
            <!-- merged output -->
            <rect x="324" y="64" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="384"
                y="82"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">merged SSTable</text
            >
            <text x="384" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >dead + deleted keys dropped</text
            >
            <!-- scoreboard -->
            <rect
                x="466"
                y="42"
                width="160"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="546"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">SCORED ON 3 AMPS</text
            >
            <text x="546" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >↑ Write amp</text
            >
            <text x="546" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >↑ Read amp</text
            >
            <text x="546" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >↑ Space amp</text
            >
            <text x="546" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >pick a policy = pick<tspan x="546" dy="11">which one you pay</tspan></text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE LSM PATH — and where compaction makes its choice</text
            >
            <line
                x1="384"
                y1="106"
                x2="464"
                y2="104"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this banner. "Just compact in the background" hides a policy choice — and that
        choice is where the engine's whole performance profile is decided.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
